Grid.

In MODE, and in MET generally, grids are represented internally as
subsets of $\Z \times \Z$.  More specifically, a grid is the set

$\left\{(x, y) \ | \ x, y \in \Z, \, 0 \leq x < N_x, \, 0 \leq y < N_y \right\}$, 

where $N_x$ and $N_y$ are the number of grid points in the $x$ and $y$ 
directions, respectively.



